on\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/37_AC\" title=\"37 AC\">37&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\n<p>Iron Throne victory\n</p>\nExtinction of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Qoherys\" title=\"House Qoherys\">House Qoherys</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/45px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/60px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a></b>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Tully.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Tully.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/20px-House_Tully.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/30px-House_Tully.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/40px-House_Tully.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">Riverlands</a>, led by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Qoherys.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Qoherys.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/52/House_Qoherys.svg/20px-House_Qoherys.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/52/House_Qoherys.svg/30px-House_Qoherys.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/52/House_Qoherys.svg/40px-House_Qoherys.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Qoherys\" title=\"House Qoherys\">House Qoherys</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></li></ul></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Hoare_2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Hoare 2.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/30px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/45px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/60px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/Harren_the_Red\" title=\"Harren the Red\">Harren the Red</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Rivers\" title=\"King of the Rivers\">King of the Rivers</a></b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Commanders</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aenys I Targaryen\">Aenys I Targaryen</a>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Tully.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Tully.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/20px-House_Tully.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/30px-House_Tully.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/61/House_Tully.svg/40px-House_Tully.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord Tully</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Stokeworth.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Stokeworth.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/20px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/30px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/40px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Stokeworth\" title=\"Alyn Stokeworth\">Alyn Stokeworth</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a></li></ul></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      King <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_the_Red\" title=\"Harren the Red\">Harren the Red</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Strength</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Outlaws</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Casualties</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gargon_Qoherys\" title=\"Gargon Qoherys\">Gargon Qoherys</a>†<br />Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Stokeworth\" title=\"Alyn Stokeworth\">Alyn Stokeworth</a>†</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_the_Red\" title=\"Harren the Red\">Harren the Red</a>†</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Harren the Red's rebellion</b> was a revolt by <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_the_Red\" title=\"Harren the Red\">Harren the Red</a> against the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/37_AC\" title=\"37 AC\">37&#160;AC</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harren_the_Red%27s_rebellion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">the Conquest</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> slew <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_Hoare\" title=\"Harren Hoare\">Harren Hoare</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_Rivers\" title=\"King of the Isles and the Rivers\">King of the Isles and the Rivers</a>, in the <a href=\"/index.php/Burning_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Burning of Harrenhal\">burning of Harrenhal</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The realm of Harren the Black was then divided between the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a>, ruled by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyjoy\" title=\"House Greyjoy\">House Greyjoy</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>, ruled by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a>. Within the riverlands, Aegon granted rule over <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Qoherys\" title=\"House Qoherys\">House Qoherys</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The lecherous <a href=\"/index.php/Gargon_Qoherys\" title=\"Gargon Qoherys\">Gargon Qoherys</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a>, was disliked for practicing the <a href=\"/index.php/First_night\" title=\"First night\">first night</a> within his domains and for taking advantage of his servants. While King <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aenys I Targaryen\">Aenys I Targaryen</a> was at <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> during a <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_progress\" title=\"Royal progress\">royal progress</a> after succeeding Aegon on the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>, the father of a maid dishonored by Gargon opened a postern gate at Harrenhal to the outlaw <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_the_Red\" title=\"Harren the Red\">Harren the Red</a>, who claimed to be Harren the Black's grandson. Gargon the Guest was killed by Red Harren in the <a href=\"/index.php/Godswood_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Godswood of Harrenhal\">godswood of Harrenhal</a>, and most of Harrenhal's men-at-arms joined the brigands. Harren called himself Lord of Harrenhal and <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Rivers\" title=\"King of the Rivers\">King of the Rivers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">Lord Tully</a> urged King Aenys to fly to Harrenhal on <a href=\"/index.php/Quicksilver\" title=\"Quicksilver\">Quicksilver</a>, his <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>, and quickly end Harren's rebellion, but Aenys instead ordered Lord Tully to call his banners. By the time Aenys eventually marched on Harrenhal with a thousand men, the castle had been abandoned with Harren fled to the woods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Aenys's reign was also troubled by <a href=\"/index.php/Jonos_Arryn%27s_rebellion\" title=\"Jonos Arryn&#39;s rebellion\">Jonos Arryn's rebellion</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lodos_the_Twice-Drowned%27s_revolt\" title=\"Lodos the Twice-Drowned&#39;s revolt\">Lodos the Twice-Drowned's revolt</a> in the Iron islands, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Dornish_War\" title=\"Second Dornish War\">Second Dornish War</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Worried that Red Harren might threaten <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, King Aenys sent Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyssa Velaryon\">Alyssa Velaryon</a> and their younger children to the safety of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Stokeworth\" title=\"Alyn Stokeworth\">Alyn Stokeworth</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, led a few hundred men,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> including <a href=\"/index.php/Myles_Smallwood\" title=\"Myles Smallwood\">Myles Smallwood</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> to hunt down Harren. The royal host eventually caught the river rebels in a village west of the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye\" title=\"Gods Eye\">Gods Eye</a>. Harren slew Lord Stokeworth and was in turn slain by Alyn's squire, <a href=\"/index.php/Bernarr_Brune\" title=\"Bernarr Brune\">Bernarr Brune</a>. Aenys rewarded Bernarr with <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knighthood</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harren_the_Red%27s_rebellion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Aegon's Conquest.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Reign of the Dragon - The Wars of King Aegon I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_t